1
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:17,400
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,680
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:40,080
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,520
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 10]

23
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,500
Mr. Li.

24
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,220
Mr. Li.

25
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:58,940
Who's knocking this early?

26
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,780
Cong?

27
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:01,820
What's going on?

28
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:02,660
Ms. Zhang,

29
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,660
is Mr. Li home?

30
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,540
Haven't seen him in a while.

31
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,540
He went to his daughter's.

32
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,010
Do you know

33
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:08,700
where that is?

34
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,170
No.

35
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,660
I need

36
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:12,620
to speak with him.

37
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,020
If you see him,

38
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:14,660
please pass that along.

39
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,180
Alright.

40
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:15,900
Or…

41
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,420
you could just tell my mom.

42
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,180
Sure.

43
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:18,860
Don't worry.

44
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:19,940
- Thanks. Bye. - Bye.

45
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:21,920
[CUSTOMS INSPECTION]

46
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:24,520
[Strong Security, Friendly Service
Strike the smuggling from you and me.]

47
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:27,040
[CHINA CUSTOMS]

48
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:03,260
Hello.

49
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,220
China Customs.

50
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,620
Please cooperate with the inspection.

51
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,340
No problem.

52
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:10,460
Your backpack, please.

53
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:11,420
And your passport.

54
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,180
Okay.

55
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,260
Your backpack.

56
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:17,540
Here.

57
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,060
Thank you.

58
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:29,660
Sir,

59
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,620
you read original English books?

60
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,700
Impressive.

61
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,220
Why two identical copies?

62
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,780
One's for a friend.

63
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,740
He said he couldn't get it in China.

64
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,820
So your English must be pretty good?

65
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,620
Let me put it this way.

66
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,420
If the 26 letters stand alone,

67
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:47,580
I can recognize them.

68
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:50,580
Put them together,

69
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:51,820
and I'm lost.

70
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,940
You've got a sense of humor.

71
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,300
Where did you buy them?

72
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,700
My friend sent me a photo.

73
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,660
I just followed it

74
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:02,700
and found the place.

75
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,100
Once I got them,

76
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,780
I deleted the photo.

77
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,140
So

78
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,780
you don't actually know
what book this is?

79
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,060
No.

80
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,380
Let me tell you then.

81
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:16,050
Its title is

82
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:17,140
Gone with the Wind.

83
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:18,300
It's been available

84
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,050
in China for a long time.

85
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:21,220
A world classic.

86
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:24,140
You can find at least six editions

87
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,820
of the English version

88
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:28,420
on major book sites

89
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,340
or at Xinhua Bookstores.

90
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,180
Not as hard to get as you think.

91
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:32,740
Is that so?

92
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:35,100
Maybe my friend

93
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,860
wanted a specific edition.

94
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,380
That's true.

95
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,300
This book

96
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,380
is indeed special.

97
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,460
If there's nothing else,

98
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,340
can I go?

99
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,100
Sorry.

100
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,540
You'll need to come with us.

101
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:48,660
Dayu.

102
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:50,820
Over here.

103
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:51,580
Sir,

104
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,020
this way.

105
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:54,980
Guo Cong.

106
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,140
Yes.

107
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,220
Go.

108
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,180
Don't stop here.

109
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,540
Keep moving.

110
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,460
Take a good look.

111
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,140
Heroin.

112
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,020
How many years is that?

113
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,100
Ask your mentor.

114
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:50,340
What's wrong?

115
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,100
Nothing.

116
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,620
You know him?

117
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:58,340
Mr. Li.

118
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,060
My neighbor.

119
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,220
Drugs hidden in the book.

120
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,340
Anti-smuggling men took him away.

121
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,140
Four boxes of alprazolam.

122
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,140
Indian generics.

123
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,900
And you just let him go?

124
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:26,820
What were you thinking?

125
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,020
After his wife passed,

126
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:30,860
Mr. Li

127
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,100
fell into depression.

128
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,940
I knew he'd been seeing a doctor.

129
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,220
His meds were all legit.

130
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:39,220
They're just cheaper overseas.

131
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,540
I checked them.

132
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,620
The quantity was fine for personal use,

133
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:43,420
so I…

134
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,180
So you didn't open the boxes,

135
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,540
check his prescription,

136
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,820
or verify any purchase records.

137
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:48,340
No.

138
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,980
What if it had been drugs?

139
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,300
He watched me grow up.

140
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,300
I didn't think he would…

141
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,260
When did I ever teach you

142
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:59,100
to judge based on assumptions?

143
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,100
Two border crossings

144
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,580
in a short time.

145
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,740
What does that tell you?

146
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,500
He's not a random,

147
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,740
last-minute mule dragged into this!

148
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:10,340
Even if

149
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,700
last time was his first offense…

150
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,300
If you'd stopped him

151
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,540
back then,

152
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,980
this might've been avoided!

153
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:17,180
His books

154
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,900
were soaked in drugs.

155
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,340
More sophisticated this time.

156
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:24,100
And a larger quantity.
He's facing severe penalties!

157
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,180
Also,

158
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,740
that 14-year-old kid

159
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,980
who got poisoned by drugs
hidden in comic books.

160
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:31,940
Do you remember him?

161
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,340
So you do.

162
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,500
He attacked his father with a chopper!

163
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,380
Sir…

164
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,460
I'm sorry.

165
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,540
Not to me!

166
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:42,820
Tell

167
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:44,140
your neighbor, Mr. Li.

168
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:46,700
Tell the people whose lives
have been destroyed by drugs.

169
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,940
You've disappointed me again and again.

170
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:57,220
I'm starting to think

171
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,180
I misjudged you.

172
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:09,740
Two border crossings

173
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,180
in a short time.

174
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,500
What does that tell you?

175
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,540
He's not a random,

176
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:15,780
last-minute mule dragged into this!

177
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,140
His books

178
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,820
were soaked in drugs.

179
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,300
More sophisticated this time.

180
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,100
And a larger quantity.
He's facing severe penalties!

181
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:27,300
These are antidepressants.

182
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,340
Prescribed by a doctor in China.

183
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:36,980
I'll kill you!

184
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:37,580
Hold him!

185
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,700
I'll kill you!

186
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,580
Stop filming!

187
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,100
My kid's sick… he's sick…

188
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:44,660
It's okay, it's okay!

189
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:45,500
Let me go…

190
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,940
On your first day in Customs,

191
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,140
I told you this.

192
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:52,220
Customs is the face of the country.

193
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,660
When you stand there,
you're not standing for yourself.

194
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:57,500
You represent the nation.

195
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,140
Uncle, I applied for leave.

196
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:14,580
So suddenly? Something going on?

197
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,340
I made a mistake.

198
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,020
A pretty basic one.

199
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,260
Well… maybe not basic,

200
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,180
but…

201
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,460
I saw my weakness.

202
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,060
That's a good thing.

203
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:28,140
Only when you see your weakness

204
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:29,420
can you fix it

205
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,100
and stay sharp in the future.

206
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:31,820
Right?

207
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:32,900
Truth is,

208
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,140
too much confidence
is just quiet arrogance.

209
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,780
Push it too far,

210
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,660
and you'll fall.

211
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:38,780
To be honest,

212
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,500
I've been waiting for you to trip up.

213
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,780
Your mentor has always had faith in you,

214
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,340
but the way he protects you

215
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,300
isn't helping you.

216
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,380
Then why didn't you warn me?

217
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:56,420
When you're that confident,
would you even listen?

218
00:09:57,820 --> 00:10:00,520
Especially with someone
like Chen Sanhe backing you up.

219
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:03,840
If something's unclear about work,

220
00:10:03,940 --> 00:10:04,960
ask the senior officers,

221
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:06,360
like Chen.

222
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:08,640
If something comes up
in your private life,

223
00:10:08,660 --> 00:10:09,440
you can come to me.

224
00:10:09,660 --> 00:10:10,360
Got it.

225
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:11,200
No matter what,

226
00:10:11,540 --> 00:10:12,760
once you join the unit…

227
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:13,720
Chief.

228
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:17,480
Did you need me?

229
00:10:21,260 --> 00:10:22,480
Take a look at this.

230
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:24,520
A complaint letter?

231
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,000
What's going on here?

232
00:10:26,020 --> 00:10:28,160
Passengers file complaints
at the drop of a hat these days.

233
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,000
You asked for him.

234
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:32,520
Not even six months

235
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:33,280
under you,

236
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:35,360
and you've got this mess?

237
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:36,200
What happened?

238
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:36,880
Chief,

239
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:39,040
last time I was on duty,

240
00:10:39,620 --> 00:10:41,160
I caught a drug-smuggling suspect.

241
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:42,000
Li Dayou.

242
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,440
After his wife died,

243
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,160
he started abusing meds

244
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:46,400
to cope

245
00:10:46,540 --> 00:10:47,800
and got hooked.

246
00:10:48,020 --> 00:10:48,840
A smuggling ring

247
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:50,920
lured him in and turned him into a mule.

248
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,320
Not long ago, he brought in

249
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:54,320
psych meds.

250
00:10:54,340 --> 00:10:55,480
Guo Cong was fooled

251
00:10:55,660 --> 00:10:56,720
and let him through.

252
00:10:56,940 --> 00:10:58,160
I caught him the second time.

253
00:10:58,620 --> 00:11:00,360
Did you find what he brought in
the first time?

254
00:11:00,380 --> 00:11:00,920
Yes.

255
00:11:00,980 --> 00:11:02,040
We tracked them down.

256
00:11:02,180 --> 00:11:03,320
Right after the arrest,

257
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:04,960
Li Dayou rolled on his supplier.

258
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:06,280
The anti-smuggling unit

259
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:07,920
recovered those drugs.

260
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:08,880
They hadn't been sold.

261
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:09,480
No worries.

262
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:10,320
Good.

263
00:11:10,620 --> 00:11:11,800
Be patient

264
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,000
with young people.

265
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,400
Guide them properly.

266
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:15,640
Yes, Chief.

267
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:17,280
You're absolutely right.

268
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:17,880
Please give me

269
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:18,960
two days.

270
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:20,000
I gotta go.

271
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:21,080
Shift change.

272
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,640
Sorry, Chief.
Didn't mean to cause trouble.

273
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:27,200
Cong,

274
00:11:27,540 --> 00:11:29,600
sometimes you only reflect

275
00:11:29,740 --> 00:11:30,760
after you've hit the wall

276
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:32,280
and felt the pain.

277
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:37,920
I'm starting to doubt my own judgment.

278
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:41,880
Now you've swung

279
00:11:42,180 --> 00:11:44,240
to the other extreme.

280
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:48,320
Passenger inspection needs
objectivity and calmness.

281
00:11:49,060 --> 00:11:50,880
But right now,
you're completely thrown off.

282
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:53,080
I don't know exactly what happened,

283
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:54,280
but listen to me.

284
00:11:54,580 --> 00:11:57,360
Don't make any decisions

285
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:58,440
while you're in this state.

286
00:12:02,740 --> 00:12:04,480
You've met my neighbor,

287
00:12:04,620 --> 00:12:05,680
Mr. Li, right?

288
00:12:06,780 --> 00:12:07,280
I have.

289
00:12:07,580 --> 00:12:08,440
Glasses,

290
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:10,360
quiet, polite. That one?

291
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:12,800
It's because of him.

292
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:14,000
I…

293
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:15,520
I ruined him.

294
00:12:17,060 --> 00:12:18,080
Ruined him?

295
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,120
That's a stretch.

296
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:32,340
Come work for me.

297
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:39,540
Cong,

298
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:41,340
what do you see?

299
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:43,340
Mules.

300
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:45,820
Look again.

301
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:51,660
Zebras.

302
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:53,700
Exactly.

303
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:54,900
So no matter when,

304
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:58,060
don't judge
based on surface impressions.

305
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,380
No matter who it is.

306
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,420
Mr. Zhang, Mr. Li,

307
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:04,780
or even me.
You can't rely on appearances.

308
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,460
You are

309
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:08,300
easily influenced by emotions.

310
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,300
That comes from your past.

311
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,580
But in Passenger Inspection,

312
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,580
you can't get controlled by emotions.

313
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,100
You have to stay calm.

314
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,220
Reflect more.

315
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,020
Challenge yourself more.

316
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:22,540
I believe you'll learn

317
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:23,900
to make the right calls.

318
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:27,580
Got it.

319
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:05,760
[Mentor]

320
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,420
I'm giving you one day
to figure this out.

321
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,700
Tomorrow, at noon.

322
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,060
Meet me at Fei's place.

323
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,140
Quit snapping shots.

324
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,460
My face is protected, you know.

325
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:55,400
Fei!

326
00:14:55,540 --> 00:14:56,080
Xiuyuan.

327
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:56,680
Killing time?

328
00:15:01,260 --> 00:15:03,440
With a view like this,

329
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:04,520
you're not taking pictures?

330
00:15:08,620 --> 00:15:09,680
Why'd you call me?

331
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:10,560
About Cong?

332
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:12,240
If it weren't about him,

333
00:15:12,260 --> 00:15:13,480
I wouldn't have bothered.

334
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:16,400
He messed up?

335
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:19,240
Still young.

336
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,400
Not enough experience.

337
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:23,040
Right now, he's full of guilt.

338
00:15:23,540 --> 00:15:25,880
Starting to seriously doubt himself.

339
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,440
Why bring me into this?

340
00:15:29,460 --> 00:15:30,240
You're his uncle.

341
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,880
This is his first real setback.

342
00:15:35,380 --> 00:15:37,280
I want the two of us to talk with him

343
00:15:37,580 --> 00:15:38,400
and give him a push.

344
00:15:39,020 --> 00:15:39,920
Got it?

345
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:58,600
[Fresh Catch Seafood]

346
00:16:10,660 --> 00:16:12,320
Here, give me a hand.

347
00:16:15,980 --> 00:16:16,560
Cong.

348
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:17,280
Fei.

349
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,320
Is Mr. Chen here?

350
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:22,360
He's been here for a while.

351
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:23,320
Cong,

352
00:16:23,940 --> 00:16:25,280
what's the occasion today?

353
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:26,560
He insisted

354
00:16:26,580 --> 00:16:28,320
on booking the whole place.

355
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:29,200
No idea.

356
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:30,520
Some kind of special day?

357
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:32,160
Come on.

358
00:16:36,420 --> 00:16:37,680
Good, you made it.

359
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:38,840
I didn't misjudge you.

360
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:41,600
So this is a setup

361
00:16:41,620 --> 00:16:43,200
for Cong, huh?

362
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,880
I'm telling you, Chen Sanhe.

363
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:50,560
He's a good kid.

364
00:16:51,060 --> 00:16:52,120
If he's made a mistake,

365
00:16:52,260 --> 00:16:54,160
that's on you as his mentor.

366
00:16:54,660 --> 00:16:56,320
Stay out of it. Get back to work.

367
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,400
Fei,

368
00:16:57,420 --> 00:16:58,440
it's not that serious.

369
00:16:58,540 --> 00:16:59,760
Not some setup.

370
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:02,800
Make Cong a bowl
of seafood offal noodles.

371
00:17:02,820 --> 00:17:03,800
Warm him up a bit.

372
00:17:03,820 --> 00:17:04,400
No problem.

373
00:17:04,610 --> 00:17:05,280
Thanks.

374
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:07,160
Cong,

375
00:17:07,820 --> 00:17:08,760
don't worry.

376
00:17:08,780 --> 00:17:09,720
I've got you.

377
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,720
Uncle, what are you doing here?

378
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:12,520
Sit.

379
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:13,520
Let's talk.

380
00:17:16,020 --> 00:17:17,040
I'm not here

381
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:20,160
to mediate between you and your mentor.

382
00:17:20,580 --> 00:17:21,880
We're here

383
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:23,200
to watch you make a choice.

384
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,000
I know.

385
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:28,200
Lost your voice?

386
00:17:28,420 --> 00:17:29,560
No, I…

387
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:30,560
I… I said it.

388
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:31,360
I know.

389
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:32,240
Know what?

390
00:17:35,580 --> 00:17:36,080
I know

391
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:37,160
I let you down.

392
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:38,360
Have I not told you?

393
00:17:38,620 --> 00:17:40,640
This is nothing next

394
00:17:40,780 --> 00:17:41,640
to national security.

395
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:42,400
Chen,

396
00:17:42,620 --> 00:17:43,680
what did we agree on?

397
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:44,320
Take it easy.

398
00:17:44,940 --> 00:17:45,440
Guo Cong,

399
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,120
I asked your uncle to come

400
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:49,280
so you can answer one question

401
00:17:49,660 --> 00:17:50,520
in front of us.

402
00:17:50,540 --> 00:17:51,800
Have you thought through

403
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,320
the mistake you made?

404
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:54,400
I know.

405
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:56,520
It was a serious mistake.

406
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,480
What I want to know is

407
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:01,040
why you chose Customs
in the first place.

408
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:05,320
When I first graduated,

409
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:06,680
I didn't know what I wanted.

410
00:18:07,060 --> 00:18:08,200
But there were two things

411
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:09,480
I knew I didn't want.

412
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,720
One was studying abroad.

413
00:18:10,740 --> 00:18:11,840
The other

414
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:13,840
was working
at my uncle's trading company.

415
00:18:16,540 --> 00:18:17,440
Dayu

416
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:18,840
was preparing
for the civil service exam,

417
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:20,560
so I followed him.

418
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:23,720
I didn't understand Customs back then.

419
00:18:24,420 --> 00:18:25,560
But these past six months

420
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,200
in Passenger Inspection,

421
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,200
I've been proud. Really proud.

422
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:31,120
I want to be like you,

423
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,200
guarding the border.

424
00:18:32,380 --> 00:18:35,400
But I keep feeling
like I'm not good enough.

425
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:41,000
Chen,

426
00:18:41,140 --> 00:18:42,920
since you asked me here today,

427
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:44,320
I'll say something.

428
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:47,520
I know Cong.

429
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:49,680
He's too soft-hearted.

430
00:18:50,780 --> 00:18:52,120
Always thinking about others.

431
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:53,240
He just can't toughen up

432
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:54,760
as you do.

433
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,480
In Customs,

434
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:57,360
what you deal with

435
00:18:57,380 --> 00:18:59,400
is either traffickers or criminals.

436
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:01,080
He hasn't had the mental buffer
for that yet.

437
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:03,480
I knew he wasn't cut out for this.

438
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:05,040
So don't push him today.

439
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:05,480
Alright?

440
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:07,920
I'm not just angry because he went soft

441
00:19:07,940 --> 00:19:09,080
and let Li Dayou slip through.

442
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:11,280
It's because he showed
no accountability.

443
00:19:13,980 --> 00:19:16,160
You protected him too much.

444
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:18,680
Yeah, a boat's safe in harbor,

445
00:19:19,380 --> 00:19:20,480
but it never faces

446
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:21,320
the waves.

447
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:22,720
Then, it's just for show!

448
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:26,800
Guo Cong, listen carefully.

449
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:27,920
No one

450
00:19:27,940 --> 00:19:30,280
in this world is born a fighter.

451
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:32,320
You get there by being tested.

452
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:34,960
Don't let him get you

453
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:36,160
all worked up.

454
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:37,000
Listen, Cong.

455
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,680
If you haven't figured it out yet,

456
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:40,160
take this time off

457
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:40,880
and go out.

458
00:19:41,220 --> 00:19:41,840
Go to Xizang,

459
00:19:41,980 --> 00:19:42,800
Xinjiang,

460
00:19:42,940 --> 00:19:44,360
or even farther, the Alps.

461
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:45,200
See the world!

462
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:46,720
Xiang Xiuyuan,
you're trying to pick a fight with me?

463
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:47,840
Enough, both of you.

464
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:50,080
Fine, fine.

465
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:54,180
What are you trying to say?

466
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:55,780
Mentor, Uncle Xiang,

467
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:56,780
please, stop arguing.

468
00:19:56,880 --> 00:19:57,660
I have my answer.

469
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:04,980
I've thought it through these days.

470
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,300
I know I was wrong.

471
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:07,460
I'll be back tomorrow.

472
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:08,460
See?

473
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:09,900
Xiang Xiuyuan,

474
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:11,820
I told you

475
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,780
Guo Cong would come around!

476
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,340
That was quick.

477
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:16,820
You've sorted it out?

478
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:17,500
It's settled.

479
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:19,220
Cong,

480
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:21,500
can't say a word
unless you're on your feet, huh?

481
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,420
It looks more powerful.

482
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:28,360
[Eight Years Later, 2023]

483
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:42,360
[China Customs]

484
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:09,280
[Canada]

485
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,420
I wanna get some whiskey.

486
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,180
Who's calling?

487
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:32,460
Why don't you answer?

488
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,380
It's my mom. I don't want to take it.

489
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,380
She still doesn't like me?

490
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,180
She doesn't even know you.

491
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:40,580
Baby.

492
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:41,140
Really.

493
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:43,340
I don't want to see
how you and your mother

494
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:45,620
are making trouble because of me.

495
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:48,180
I don't want to be like this.

496
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:50,140
But she always thinks

497
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,860
negatively about people.

498
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,540
Qian,

499
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:55,060
you're coming back next week.

500
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:56,300
Have you packed yet?

501
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:58,860
Call me when you get a chance.

502
00:21:58,860 --> 00:22:00,400
[Canceled]

503
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:06,540
I have an idea. Next week,
you are going to China, right?

504
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,660
So how about I and you go together?

505
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:12,540
And we give your mother a chance
to see how I am.

506
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:14,340
Really?

507
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,660
That will be great.

508
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,020
Likely, I have a chance
to go to Myanmar.

509
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,340
So you can go with me,

510
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:22,940
and then from there, we'll go to China.

511
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:25,260
We'll not tell your mom first.

512
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:27,340
Let's make quite a surprise for her.

513
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,540
Thanks, honey.

514
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:36,500
Li,

515
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:38,020
you are beautiful,

516
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:39,380
and you've got skills.

517
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,100
I really admire

518
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:43,460
how

519
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,660
hands-on

520
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,660
you are.

521
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,300
Save that line

522
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:50,700
for charming young girls.

523
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:54,020
Christmas is coming.

524
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,940
How's your holiday stock looking?

525
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:58,220
Don't worry.

526
00:22:58,320 --> 00:22:59,180
These birds,

527
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:01,020
raised with love,

528
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:02,300
are on their way home.

529
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:28,840
[CHINA CUSTOMS]

530
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:39,300
Can you check how much duty I still owe?

531
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:40,100
Sure.

532
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:50,580
Mr. Guo,

533
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,900
so many young ladies on this flight.

534
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,300
Schools abroad are on winter break.

535
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,140
And students heading home

536
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:59,580
often route through Southeast Asia

537
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:00,780
for cheaper fares.

538
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:03,300
Look at them,

539
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,700
all carrying down jackets.

540
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:08,020
And those luggage tags

541
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,580
are all from European
or American airports.

542
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:14,100
All units, heads up.

543
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,620
Many students took this flight back.

544
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:19,140
Watch for anyone carrying luxury items

545
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,100
over the duty-free limit.

546
00:24:21,120 --> 00:24:21,900
- Copy that. - Copy that.

547
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:40,660
Miss,

548
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:42,620
that item needs to be inspected as well.

549
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:44,620
They're just some oil paintings.

550
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:45,540
They also need inspection.

551
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,020
How about this?

552
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:48,100
I'll open it for you.

553
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:55,860
See?

554
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:58,220
Just oil paintings.

555
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:08,940
Alright,

556
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:09,780
please come with me.

557
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:11,340
We need to check your luggage.

558
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:13,700
It's just clothes.

559
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:14,980
It won't take long.

560
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:16,020
This way, please.

561
00:25:34,520 --> 00:25:35,020
Hello.

562
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:36,660
Ma'am.

563
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:49,940
All set?

564
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:51,180
Still not done?

565
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:58,500
Your luggage is clear.

566
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:12,940
- Then, I'll…
- Let me take a look at this.

567
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:16,460
But you've already checked it.

568
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:18,060
Routine check, please cooperate.

569
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:21,820
Fine, I'll open it.

570
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:55,220
Let me help you.

571
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,220
No, I've got it.

572
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:56,900
I'll help you.

573
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:00,100
This is my art tube.

574
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:11,460
I always pack it this way.

575
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:28,900
Miss,

576
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,500
you can't leave right now.

577
00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:07,060
Easy.

578
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,220
A hidden compartment.

579
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:50,960
Helmeted hornbill casque.

580
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,940
Your passport and ticket, please.

581
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:07,700
Xiao Jing.

582
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:09,260
What do you do?

583
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:11,740
I'm a student.

584
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:13,860
In Myanmar?

585
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:14,660
No,

586
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:16,260
I study in Edinburgh.

587
00:29:17,880 --> 00:29:18,940
Do you know what this is?

588
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:21,220
Yes.

589
